               <p>SAMUEL BOLTON. I am a <rs id="t18281204-253-viclabel1339" type="occupation">coal-dealer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-253-victim2186 t18281204-253-viclabel1339"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281204-253-crimeloc1340">Abbott's-place, Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-253-crimeloc1340" type="placeName" value="Abbott's-place, Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-253-crimeloc1340" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-253-off1337 t18281204-253-crimeloc1340"></join>. The prisoner borrowed a truck of me at a quarter-past two o'clock on the 27th of November - he said he wanted it for Cohen, who lived not one hundred yards off, for two hours.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-253-person2187">
                  MANNING 
                  ROWLAND
               <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2187" type="surname" value="ROWLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2187" type="given" value="MANNING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2187" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 27th of November, about a quarter-past three o'clock, I went to Smithfield, and saw the prisoner dragging a truck; he had just left some person, who had been looking at it: when he came up to me I asked him if he had bought it - he said No, he had got it for sale; I asked what he wanted for it - he said 12s.; I said "It is not just such a thing as suits me" - he said, "I will sell it for 10s.;" I offered him 7s. - he said if I liked it at three half-crowns I should have it; I bought it at last for 7s. - I knew him before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-253-person2188">
                  CHARLES 
                  RICKETTS
               <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2188" type="surname" value="RICKETTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2188" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-253-person2188" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner in Pitfield-street on the 28th; I saw the truck, and shewed the same to the prosecutor, who accused the prisoner of stealing it, which he denied.</p>
               <p>SAMUEL BOLTON re-examined. Q.Did you know him before? A. No; he was with me the first time about two minutes, and then came again and staid about the same time - I am positive he is the person; I met him in the street; I put my hand on his shoulder, and asked how he came to sell my truck in Smithfield; he said,"Don't handle me;" I saw the officer and gave him in charge; I knew Rowland; I met him, and told him I had lost my truck; he said, "I dare say I have bought it."</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I made no resistance; I was at home that day from twelve o'clock, and never went out: I know nothing about it.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
